subsection.def:
instructions
                    (指示) means administrative instructions issued
                by the Director under section 5;

lodged
                    (送交) means delivered to and accepted by the
                Registrar in accordance with this Ordinance;

master
                    (船長) includes every person (except a pilot)
                having command or charge of any ship;

register
                    (註冊紀錄冊) means the register of ships kept
                under section 7;

registered
                    (註冊), in relation to a ship, means registered
                under this Ordinance;

registrable
                    (可註冊), in relation to a ship, means able to
                be registered under this Ordinance;

subsection.content:
The protection conferred on public officers by subsection (1) in respect of any
                act or omission shall not in any way affect any liability of the Government in tort
                for that act or omission. (Amended 64 of 1999 s. 3)

paragraph.content:
being a ship registered by virtue of subsection (1)(a), a
                    majority interest in the ship ceases to be owned by one or more qualified
                    persons;

subparagraph.content:
the ship ceases to be operated under a demise charter by a body
                        corporate being a qualified person (whether by reason of the termination of
                        the demise charter or otherwise);

paragraph.content:
providing for the measurement and survey of ships for the purpose of
                    ascertaining tonnage to be undertaken, in such circumstances as may be specified
                    in the regulations, by or on behalf of a Certifying Authority;

making any provision of the regulations dependent on compliance with such
                    conditions, to be evidenced in such manner, as may be specified in the
                    regulations;

requiring the name by which it is proposed to register a ship to be
                    approved by the Registrar before the name is marked on the ship or entered in
                    the register;

in the case of one or more individuals, by that or those persons, as the
                    case may be, or by an individual or individuals appointed to act on his or their
                    behalf;

subparagraph.content:
(for a body corporate other than a re-domiciled company) its registration under
              Part 16 of the Companies Ordinance (Cap. 622)
              (Cap. 622);

paragraph.content:
a statement that to the best of the declarant’s knowledge and belief a majority
          interest in the ship will upon registration be owned by one or more qualified
          persons;

a statement that the ship is not registered in any place outside Hong Kong or, if
          it is so registered, that the declarant will secure deletion of the ship from the register
          in every such place;

a statement that the ship is not registered in any place outside Hong Kong or, if
          it is so registered, that the declarant will secure deletion of the ship from the register
          in every such place;

subparagraph.content:
a certificate of registration issued under Part XI of the Companies Ordinance
              (Cap. 32) as in force from time to time before 3 March
            2014;

a certificate of registration issued under Part XI of the Companies Ordinance
              (Cap. 32) as in force from time to time before 3 March
            2014;

(for a body corporate other than a re-domiciled company) a certificate of
            registration issued under Part 16 of Cap.
            622;

paragraph.content:
the documents and information specified in section 21(1)(a)(i),
                    (ii) and (iv), (b) and (c), or (3)(a)(i), (ii) and (iv), (b), (c) and (d), as
                    the case may be;

subsection.def:
mortgage
                    (抵押) means a mortgage registered under this
                Part;

mortgagee
                    (抵押權人) means the person whose name appears in
                the register as the holder of a mortgage;

obligation
                    (義務) includes any present or future
                obligation;

paragraph.content:
that, having regard to the matters mentioned in section 22(3)(a)
                    or (b) or (4), it would be inappropriate for the ship to continue to be
                    registered;

section.def:
Cap. 415C (《第415C章》) means the
            Merchant Shipping (Registration) (Tonnage) Regulations (Cap. 415
                sub. leg. C);

certifying authority (核證當局)—(a)for an International Tonnage Certificate (1969)—means a Certifying
                    Authority referred to in regulation 2A of Cap. 415C;(b)for any other listed certificate—means the Director or the
                    Registrar;

e-cert database (電子證書資料庫), in relation to a certifying authority, means an electronic
            database that is maintained or managed by or for the certifying authority in accordance
            with the e-cert guidelines;

e-cert guidelines (電子證書指引) means the documents listed in Part 3 of Schedule 4A, as
            from time to time revised or amended by revisions or amendments to those
            documents;

International Tonnage Certificate
                (1969) (1969年國際噸位證明書) means an
            International Tonnage Certificate (1969) referred to in regulation 9 of Cap. 415C;

paragraph.content:
fees for surveys, inspections, and other services and facilities provided,
                    whether in Hong Kong or elsewhere, under or for the purposes of sections
                        14 and 18;

fees for the official signature of the Director or Registrar or of any
                    person on behalf of the Director or Registrar for the purposes of this
                    Ordinance;
